      "amount": "1 large",
      "notes": "juice and zest"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "to taste",
      "notes": "adjust after adding lemon"
    },
    {
      "name": "fresh cilantro",
      "amount": "2 tbsp, chopped",
      "notes": "for garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Rinse the lentils under cold water and set aside.",
    "Heat the sesame seed oil in a saucepan over medium heat and sauté the onion until translucent, about 4 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for 30 seconds until fragrant.",
    "Stir in the cumin, turmeric, curry powder and a pinch of salt, cooking for 1 minute.",
    "Add the lentils, diced tomatoes and vegetable broth, bring to a gentle boil, then reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes until the lentils are tender.",
    "Remove the pot from heat, stir in the lemon zest and juice, and season with additional salt if needed.",
    "Divide the curry evenly into six ramekins, garnish each with chopped cilantro.",
    "Serve immediately as a warm, citrusy main dish."
  ],
